  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Derby is on a bed and breakfast or half board basis. </p>
<p>Fuel up for the day with a varied hot and cold breakfast buffet with classic continental offerings.</p>
<p>When you have returned from a day of skiing, a four course evening meal including a salad buffet is served in the Derby dining room. There is also a weekly fondue meal alternative available, so you can sample some classic Swiss cuisine. </p>
<p>If you fancy treating yourself to an<span> à la carte meal, the Föhrenstube is an excellent choice, serving a range of traditional alpine dishes.  </span>The 'CAVA'  is a traditional fondue restaurant with rustic charm - it is an excellent spot to sample the various fondues available (pay locally).</p>
<p>After a day of skiing, the Gaststube is a cosy and traditional café-bar, where locals and guests meet to enjoy a drink or two. There is also a hotel bar, where you can enjoy a weekly guest aperitif with hotel directors in hotel bar including light snacks (pay locally).</p>
<p>Christmas Gala and New Years Gala are included.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
