  <description><![CDATA[<p>Expect great quality service and a warm welcome at the Derby Hotel, returning guests feel personally valued by the family and staff here. Ideally positioned in <a data-udi="umb://document/f6cb1f0178b7447488bbf36b5f109fbc" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f6cb1f0178b7447488bbf36b5f109fbc}" title="Grindelwald">Grindelwald, </a>you can take advantage of the magnificent mountain views and hassle free ski links.</p>
<h2>Hearty cuisine</h2>
<p>The Derby offers you a wide range of options, whether you are fuelling up for a day on the slopes or looking for a spot for lunch or an après drink, there is something for everyone.</p>
<p>An extensive breakfast buffet with a range of options including a classic continental offering is served each morning and when you have returned from a day on the slopes a delicious evening meal awaits you -plus once a week you can enjoy a traditional fondue evening.</p>
<p>If you want to treat yourself to a traditional Swiss fondue 'Cava' is an excellent choice,  serving a variety of fondues in a rustic style cellar restaurant. Alternatively the <span>à la carte</span>  <span>Föhrenstube</span> has a range of Bernese specialities and classic favourites on the menu.</p>
<p>When you have returned for the day head to the Gaststube - a spot where locals and tourists gather to enjoy a drinks or two in a cosy café-bar. </p>
<h2>Great location</h2>
<p>With a central location in Grindelwald, getting around the <a data-udi="umb://document/1a5883a1530346a9ab78607d76c2e656" href="/{localLink:umb://document/1a5883a1530346a9ab78607d76c2e656}" title="Jungfrau Ski Region">Jungfrau Region</a> couldn't be easier. The village railway is conveniently located just opposite the hotel, and the bus station is just a short walk away - catch the bus to the First gondola and head up the active mountain, ski the day away or fly through the alps on a 800 metre long zip line - there is also a viewing platform with incredible views of the surrounding mountain peaks.</p>
<p>You can also head to the Grindelwald Terminal station by bus or train, from here you can head up the Eiger Glacier or make your way over to <a data-udi="umb://document/7e163ac5c9114f0dae9f3f8d222fa730" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7e163ac5c9114f0dae9f3f8d222fa730}" title="Wengen">Wengen</a> via the <span>Männlichen gondola.</span></p>]]></description>
