  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Standard 'Cosy' Twin Rooms</strong> are around <span>13-15 m²</span>, sleeping two people. These rooms have a shower and most have a North facing balcony.</p>
<p><strong>Superior 'Scenic' Twin Rooms</strong> are around <span>18-20 m²</span>, sleeping up to three people. These rooms are have a bath and have a south facing balcony with views towards Mount Eiger and the valley.</p>
<p><strong>Junior suites</strong> are around 25-28m² and can sleep up to three using an extra double sofa bed, with either a north or south facing view. These rooms are on request so please give our Reservations team a call to book.</p>
<p><strong>Single rooms </strong>are around 12-13m² sleeping one person, and have a shower. These rooms are North or South facing and some have balconies but these can not be guaranteed.</p>
<p><strong>Room facilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Satellite TV</li>
<li>Wi-Fi</li>
<li>Fridge</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Tea and coffee making facilities</li>
<li>Cots are available</li>
</ul>]]></roomsDescription>
